defaultxtractio
defaultn was published by Public Health England in October. The 
defaultreport
default found that 
defaultf
defaultracking for shale gas is safe as long as operations are well-regulated and well-run
default and 
defaultthat the risks to public health from exposure to emissions from shale gas extraction are low
default. 
defaultThe report provides welcome reassurance to people
default about hydraulic fracturing 
defaultand should dispel scaremongering about its safety
default.
