default4. defaultWhether the current regulatory regime covering such activity is adequate;default4.1 The onshore oil and gas industry has a great deal of heritage in the UK. It is a fallacy posited by some that the UK lacks experience in the sector and that the regulatory system
default is not up to the ta
defaultsk. 
defaultIn the UK 
default2000 
defaultonshore 
defaultwells have since been drilled, with 200 hydraulically fractured. The UK is also home to Europe’s largest onshore oil field in Wytch Farm. 
default&#xa0;
default4.2 
defaultCuadrilla is confident that the regulatory framework in the UK is 
defaultsufficiently robust to ensure safe and responsible exploitation of shale gas. T
defaulthere is a clear scientific and academic consensus, underlined here in the UK by the Royal Society and the Royal
default Academy of Engineering joint report (
defaulthttp://royalsociety.org/policy/projects/shale-gas-extraction/report/
default), and by other prominent academic experts that unconventional oi
defaultl and gas exploration and production can be carried out entirely safely in the UK.  Concerns that have been raised around water and air contamination and seismicity can all be managed by strong regulation and industry best practice. 
default&#xa0;
default4.3 
defaultThe Government ar
defaultgues and we agree that the oil and gas regulatory process in the UK is already the strongest in the world. 
